textline.data: • REQ-7.1: The watchdog task shall operate as long as the battery level is sufficient to power the microcontroller.
• REQ-7.1: If the battery level is too low to sustain the microcontroller, the system shall safely shut down.
• REQ-6.2.1: The watchdog task shall have the highest priority in the system.
• REQ-6.2.2: TM construction tasks shall be preempted if a new TC is received.
• REQ-6.1.1: The watchdog task shall operate with a periodicity of 10ms.
• REQ-6.1.2: The deciphering and enciphering of TCs and TMs shall not exceed 100ms per operation.
• REQ-6.1.Timing Constraints
• REQ-4.1 Data Integrity Requirements
• REQ-4.1.1: The system shall compute and store a CRC for each block of data written to memory.
• REQ-4.1.2: The system shall read and validate the CRC for each block of data before processing.
• REQ-4.1.3: If a CRC mismatch is detected during memory read operations, the software shall flag the data as corrupted and take corrective actions.
• REQ-3.1 Task Management Requirements
• REQ-3.1.1: The system shall trigger a task upon receiving a deciphered TC to handle the request.
• REQ-3.1.2: The request handling task shall read data from the appropriate sensors to build the TM response packet.
• REQ-2.1 The System handles Safety and Reliability Requirements
• REQ-2.1.1: A dedicated microcontroller shall execute a watchdog task to monitor all other software tasks.
• REQ-2.1.2: The watchdog task shall send a signal to all other tasks every 10ms to ensure they are responsive.
• REQ-2.1.3: If one or more tasks fail to respond within the allotted time, the system (excluding the watchdog) shall be restarted.
• REQ-2.1.4: The watchdog shall remain operational as long as the battery level is sufficient to power the microcontroller.
• REQ-1.3.1: The system shall monitor the following parameters of the space-based system: (3D position,Temperature,Battery level,Fuel quantity)
• REQ-1.3.2: The system shall construct a TM response packet containing requested safety data upon receiving a valid TC.
• REQ-1.2.1: The system shall support sending TeleMetry (TMs) via the RF transmitter.
• REQ-1.2.2: The software shall encipher all TMs before sending them.
• REQ-1.1.1: The system shall support receiving TeleCommands (TCs) via the RF receiver.
• REQ-1.1.2: All received TCs shall be deciphered by the software before further processing.
• REQ-1.1.3: The system shall store deciphered TCs in an intermediate buffer before processing.
• REQ-1.1.4: If a new TC is received while a TM is under construction, the system shall cancel the ongoing TM and process the latest TC.
• REQ-1.1: The System handles communication requirements
The System shall monitor the Safety Data of a space-based system
